        <p> <b>Links for the didjeridu/yidaki and related material</b>



        </p><p> 



        </p><ul>



          <li>The <a href="http://www.didjshop.com/">Didj Shop site</a> has a 



            broad range of information about the didjeridu/ yidaki. Its manager, 



            <a href="http://www.didjshop.com/didjshop-team.html">Svargo Freitag</a> 



          is collaborating with this lab on the acoustics of yidaki.          </li><li><a href="http://www.yirrkala.com/yidaki/dhawu/index.html">Yidakiwuy Dhawu Miwatjnurunydja</a>, from the Yolngu people of North Eastern Arnhem Land,  has  information about the didjeridu and Yolngu culture in text and in video clips.
          </li><li>Home page of <a href="https://www.williambarton.com.au">William Barton</a>, 



            one of Australia's best known yidaki/didjeridu soloists.<br />
        </li></ul>



